 YINCHUAN, Nov. 27 (Xinhua) -- The COVID-19 vaccination for children aged between 3 and 11 in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, started here on Friday. To improve efficiency, a number of vaccination sites have been set up. Children can choose the nearest one and get inoculated at different time based on their grades, classes, etc. Detailed inoculation specifications are strictly obeyed at all vaccination sites to ensure children's security.  Photo taken on Nov. 27, 2021 shows a vaccination site in Yinchuan, northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Feng Kaihua)  Photo taken on Nov. 27, 2021 shows a vaccination site in Yinchuan, northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Feng Kaihua)  Photo taken on Nov. 27, 2021 shows a vaccination site in Yinchuan, northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Feng Kaihua) Photo taken on Nov. 27, 2021 shows a vaccination site in Yinchuan, northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Feng Kaihua)  Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ– 